j-c-VwBi0q9t62xA4QcBBUoEX834NB1wBHKQx4VdfJr-v7sMD5xSgUfPTC953mE4LqbM0X5GqmfmjhgrMt6HNiufhTiWy8zqNkSQo8zw8rNb28=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing native image issues**\\n\\nI’m looking into why the native image doesn't include the SecurityManager class despite compiling. There seems to be a potential issue with reflective invocation needing metadata, especially with the way the user-code-filter is set up. It might exclude metadata for test methods. I’m also considering how the GraalVM internal plugin handles these conditions and whether it distinguishes application code correctly. It feels like I’m navigating a bit of a maze here, but I'm on it!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Optimizing test strategies**\\n\\nI’m considering whether direct reflection is really necessary in the tests. It seems I might not need to hardcode versions either. I want a one-to-one mapping with dynamic reporting, especially with the DisposableBeanAdapterTest class. Since it’s in the support package, I’ll organize my test files properly. Maintaining coverage for each dynamic-access class in dedicated Java test files is essential. I’ll also refine my tests to ensure all dynamic-access calls are executed. There’s a potential concern about inferred close beans not being AutoCloseable, yet they have a public close method.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Identifying potential issues**\\n\\nI'm noticing a potential concern with the value of `AbstractBeanDefinition.INFER_METHOD` being set to \\\"(inferred).\\\" Also, I’m wondering if calling `destroySingletons()` and catching exceptions could create issues — but it seems like it won't. If the first `getBean` uses type instead of name in a situation with multiple beans, that might be a problem, but only for one. Finally, I need a note about existing uncommitted changes — that should be mentioned if it's relevant.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented a dedicated active-class coverage test:\n\n- Added `tests/src/org.springframework/spring-beans/5.3.15/src/test/java/org_springframework/spring_beans/DisposableBeanAdapterTest.java`\n\nCoverage paths exercised:\n- Inferred public `close()` destroy method.\n- Inferred public `shutdown()` destroy method after `close()` lookup misses.\n- Public custom destroy method resolution when non-public access is disabled.\n- Custom destroy invocation under an installed `SecurityManager` when the runtime supports installing one, with normal invocation still asserted otherwise.\n\nI did not run compilation or tests, per instruction. Note: there were pre-existing uncommitted changes/untracked files in the worktree (`ConstructorResolverTest.java` and `metadata/org.springframework/spring-beans/5.3.15/`) that I did not modify.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0601c5c51d84452e016a40591b30e881938c5ae297292f4568\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1026, "output": 1208, "cacheRead": 28672, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30906, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782601995312, "responseId": "resp_0601c5c51d84452e016a40590beff081938527bfad5f2dabd1"}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Analyzing native image issues**\n\nI’m looking into why the native image doesn't include the SecurityManager class despite compiling. There seems to be a potential issue with reflective invocation needing metadata, especially with the way the user-code-filter is set up. It might exclude metadata for test methods. I’m also considering how the GraalVM internal plugin handles these conditions and whether it distinguishes application code correctly. It feels like I’m navigating a bit of a maze here, but I'm on it!\n\n**Optimizing test strategies**\n\nI’m considering whether direct reflection is really necessary in the tests. It seems I might not need to hardcode versions either. I want a one-to-one mapping with dynamic reporting, especially with the DisposableBeanAdapterTest class. Since it’s in the support package, I’ll organize my test files properly. Maintaining coverage for each dynamic-access class in dedicated Java test files is essential. I’ll also refine my tests to ensure all dynamic-access calls are executed. There’s a potential concern about inferred close beans not being AutoCloseable, yet they have a public close method.\n\n**Identifying potential issues**\n\nI'm noticing a potential concern with the value of `AbstractBeanDefinition.INFER_METHOD` being set to \"(inferred).\" Also, I’m wondering if calling `destroySingletons()` and catching exceptions could create issues — but it seems like it won't. If the first `getBean` uses type instead of name in a situation with multiple beans, that might be a problem, but only for one. Finally, I need a note about existing uncommitted changes — that should be mentioned if it's relevant.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0601c5c51d84452e016a40590ceb6481938aa9d3c666902bf0\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQFkbfxwqxIccXTlr9UECqi-MNReWlEIacw6CglmacVtqlaCB5qeZMfcGyMeXYgZKDxAK